sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Client
    participant Global as Global Tower Layers
    participant Router as Axum Router
    participant Identity as Auth or Tenant Middleware
    participant Handler
    participant Policy as RBAC and Domain Services
    participant Data as PostgreSQL and RLS
    participant Effects as Redis, Files, Providers, or Webhooks

    Client->>Global: Request
    Global->>Router: Timeout, headers, CORS, compression, ID, tracing
    alt Public handler
        Router->>Handler: Extract path, query, headers, or body
    else Authenticated handler
        Router->>Identity: Validate bearer access token
        Identity->>Handler: Claims
    else Tenant-protected handler
        Router->>Identity: Validate token and organization membership
        Identity->>Identity: Apply rate and quota gates
        Identity->>Handler: Claims and TenantContext
    end
    Handler->>Handler: Deserialize and validate request
    Handler->>Policy: Check role, ownership, workflow, and domain rules
    Policy->>Data: Tenant-scoped or explicit global persistence
    Data-->>Policy: Rows or error
    opt Cross-system side effect
        Policy->>Effects: Cache, file, provider, audit, preview, or webhook action
        Effects-->>Policy: Result
    end
    Policy-->>Handler: Domain result
    alt Success
        Handler-->>Global: Typed response
    else AppError
        Handler-->>Global: Status and JSON ErrorBody
    end
    Global-->>Client: HTTP response or WebSocket upgrade
